page.title: 09WILDLIFE
page.content: In a predominantly rural area with a number of woods and open spaces criss-crossed by many footpaths, wildlife, both flora and fauna, are to be found in abundance. More common species are listed below. {ANIMALS Badger, bat, fieldmouse, fox, hedgehog, muntjac deer, rat, squirrel, stoat, weasel. {BIRDS} Blackbird,bluetit,coot,cuckoo,duck great-tit,jay,magpie,moorhen,owl, pheasant,robin,rook,sparrow,thrush, sparrowhawk,wren,yellowhammer,wagtail, woodpecker,pigeon, {TREES} Ash,beech,birch,cherry,chestnut,elm, fir,oak,holly,hazel,hornbeam,lime, mountain-ash,plane,sycamore {PLANTS}A wealth of indigenous plants and grasses can be found in this area.
